text: Oakohay Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Oakohay is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "mud potato". Variant names are "Coahay Creek", "Cohay Creek", "Oakahay Creek", "Ochahay Creek", and "Ocohay Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Covington County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Smith County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Scott County, Mississippi
